<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Although the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Cantharis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cantharis confossicollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confossicollis">
<pageBreakToken pageId="7" pageNumber="8" start="start">Cantharis</pageBreakToken>
confossicollis
</taxonomicName>
was attached with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Wittmer’s">Wittmer's</normalizedToken>
manuscript label &quot; 
<taxonomicName genus="Athem" lsidName="Athem ellus subsp. confossicollis" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="subSpecies" species="ellus" subSpecies="confossicollis">Athem ellus confossicollis</taxonomicName>
(Fairm.)&quot;, it has never been published formally for this taxonomic change. In our opinion, this speciesis definitely a member of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Lycocerus</taxonomicName>
due to the following characters: pronotum subquadrate, all tarsal claws simple and the aedeagus with dorsal plates of parameres separated. At the same time, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus multiimpressus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multiimpressus">Lycocerus multiimpressus</taxonomicName>
(Wittmer, 1997) is considered to be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus confossicollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confossicollis">Lycocerus confossicollis</taxonomicName>
(Fairmaire, 1891), comb. n., since we could not find differences between both nominal species in their morphological characters, including appearance and aedeagus. Therefore, we suggest 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus multiimpressus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multiimpressus">Lycocerus multiimpressus</taxonomicName>
is a new subjective synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1889" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1889" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Lycocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Lycocerus confossicollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confossicollis">Lycocerus confossicollis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
